&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role matters:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Public Sector Capture Manager is essentially the &quot;general&quot; of a specific high-value deal. Unlike a standard sales role that focuses on the volume of leads, a Capture Manager is responsible for the strategic pursuit of a single, complex government contract (often $50M+) from the early intelligence phase through to the final award.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Their primary goal is to maximize the Probability of Win (Pwin) by shaping the requirements before the Request for Proposal (RFP) is even released.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will require frequent travel to Government Clients, most of which are in the DC Area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ivanti empowers organisations to manage and secure technology smarter through our AI‑powered Ivanti Neurons platform. We help IT and Security teams reduce complexity, work proactively, and deliver better outcomes at scale for customers around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ivanti helps organisations work smarter through Autonomous Endpoint Management powered by our AI‑driven Ivanti Neurons platform—delivering better outcomes for our customers by reducing complexity and enabling proactive IT and security operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, your work will support Ivanti’s mission to enable &lt;strong&gt;Autonomous Endpoint Management&lt;/strong&gt; and deliver better outcomes for our customers. You’ll contribute to solutions that help IT and Security teams move away from manual, reactive work towards smarter, more proactive operations. Your impact will be tangible—shaping customer experience, improving product capability, and supporting scalable, resilient outcomes. You’ll work as part of a collaborative team where your contribution matters every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Be Doing:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Planning: Developing a comprehensive &quot;Capture Plan&quot; that outlines the win strategy, value proposition, and specific discriminators that set your company apart.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer Relationship Management: Building and maintaining deep relationships with government stakeholders, including Program Managers, Contracting Officers, and End Users, to understand their &quot;pain points.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Intelligence: Analyzing competitors past performance, pricing strategies, and likely teaming arrangements to position your solution effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaming &amp;amp; Partnership: Identifying and negotiating with potential subcontractors or prime partners (especially small businesses to meet socio-economic requirements).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal Orchestration: Leading cross-functional teams - including Solution Architects, Pricing, Legal, and Proposal Managers - to ensure the technical and financial offer is both compliant and compelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gate Reviews: Presenting progress to executive leadership at various &quot;decision gates&quot; (e.g., Interest, Pursuit, Preliminary Bid, Final Bid) to secure internal resources and funding for the pursuit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 6-10+ years in federal/public sector business development or capture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge: Deep understanding of FAR/DFARS (Federal Acquisition Regulations) and agency-specific procurement cycles (DoD, IC, or Civilian).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acumen: Proficiency in “Price-to-Win” (PTW) modeling and competitive assessment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Bachelor’s degree (Business or Technical); Master’s or PMP/Shipley certification preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearance: Often requires Secret, TS/SCI, or Public Trust depending on the agency focus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Ivanti?&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;In this role, you will help create a workplace experience that enables Ivanti employees, customers, and visitors to do their best work. As part of our Global Workplace Solutions (GWS) team, you will ensure our Australia office remains a safe, welcoming, and well-organized environment that supports productivity, collaboration, and business success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your work will have a direct impact on employee experience, operational efficiency, and the smooth running of day-to-day office activities. From supporting workplace operations and vendor relationships to coordinating meetings and welcoming visitors, you will play a vital role in keeping our workplace running seamlessly.&amp;nbsp;This is a part-time, in-office position working Monday to Friday from 8:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary on-site point of contact for workplace operations, ensuring the office runs smoothly and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support employees, leaders, and visitors through exceptional customer service, meeting coordination, and day-to-day office administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage workplace services, including security, cleaning, waste management, catering, postage, parking, and office supplies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate meeting room schedules and support the planning and execution of onsite meetings and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the local property management company and third-party vendors to maintain high workplace standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support VIP visits and provide a professional and welcoming experience for employees, customers, and guests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve workplace operations, enhance employee experience, and support cost-effective facilities management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 2 years of experience in facilities coordination, workplace operations, office administration, or a similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer service mindset with a proactive and solution-oriented approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple priorities simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently while collaborating effectively with broader teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Microsoft Office applications, including Outlook, Word, Excel, and Teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of professionalism and discretion when handling confidential information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting a global organization or distributed workforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing vendor relationships and coordinating workplace services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with workplace health, safety, and compliance practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting executive or VIP visitors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Ivanti&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Friendly, flexible working model: We support work-life balance while empowering employees to do their best work.&lt;br&gt;Competitive total rewards: Comprehensive health, wellness, and financial benefits designed to support you and your family.&lt;br&gt;Global, diverse teams: Collaborate with talented colleagues across more than 23 countries.&lt;br&gt;Learning and development: Grow your skills with access to best-in-class learning resources and career development opportunities.&lt;br&gt;Equity and belonging: We value every voice and believe diverse perspectives help us build better solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What drives us&lt;/str

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to join a Fast-Growing Company?&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/em&gt;Are you a strategic sales leader with a proven background in&amp;nbsp;driving high-impact growth within Federal Clients? We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Federal &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Director&lt;/strong&gt; – to own some of our Federal accounts, build trusted executive relationships and advance Ivanti&#39;s offering in the space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is remote based but requires someone located near to or within the Beltway region (D.C, Virginia, Maryland).&amp;nbsp; The nature of this role is that customers will predominantly be within the D.C Region and on site visits are an important part of flourishing relationships between us and and those customers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
